.TH "kthread_create_on_cpu" 9 "kthread_create_on_cpu" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
kthread_create_on_cpu \- Create a cpu bound kthread
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct task_struct *" kthread_create_on_cpu
.BI "(int (*threadfn)(void *data) "  ","
.BI "void *data "  ","
.BI "unsigned int cpu "  ","
.BI "const char *namefmt "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "threadfn" 12
the function to run until signal_pending(current).
.IP "data" 12
data ptr for \fIthreadfn\fP.
.IP "cpu" 12
The cpu on which the thread should be bound,
.IP "namefmt" 12
printf-style name for the thread. Format is restricted
to "name.*u". Code fills in cpu number.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This helper function creates and names a kernel thread
